Reasoning: The paper deals with the expressive power and closure properties of finite-state automata with multiple tapes, which are commonly studied in the field of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The paper also discusses algorithms and complexity results, which are typical topics in the subfields of data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of under-approximations and conditions for constructing complete intersections suggests a connection to the area of logic and verification (cs.LO), while the focus on recognizing polyadic predicates on words suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT).
